# wm/warmup -- programs to pre-load (and, under `emu -c1`, JIT-compile) at boot
# so they launch instantly later.  One program per line; blank lines and lines
# beginning with '#' are ignored.  Names are resolved like wm menu commands:
# a bare name or wm/<name> is found under /dis (e.g. "charon" -> /dis/charon.dis,
# "wm/sh" -> /dis/wm/sh.dis).
#
# The default list is everything in the wm launch menu (and submenus) -- the
# programs a user is most likely to reach for -- so they are warm by the time
# the desktop is up.  Under -c1 each is compiled in the BACKGROUND (the splash
# keeps animating); the animation speeds up as the list is worked through.
#
# Per-user override: copy this to $home/lib/warmup and edit.  Trim the list (or
# empty the file) if you would rather boot faster than pre-warm everything.

# top-level menu
wm/sh
acme
wm/edit
charon
wm/man
wm/ftree

# System submenu
wm/deb
wm/rt
wm/task
wm/memory
wm/about

# Misc submenu
wm/coffee
wm/colors
wm/date

# Games submenu
wm/tetris
wm/bounce
wm/rayteapot
